JOHANNESBURG - Bafana Bafana midfielder Hlompho Kekana has been granted compassionate leave after suffering a family bereavement. READ: Crunch time for Bafana ahead of World Cup qualifiers SAFA spokesperson Dominic Chimhavi confirmed that as a result of a family tragedy, the Sundowns midfielder Kekana has been allowed to leave the team’s Polokwane camp and return home. Bafana Bafana coach Stuart Baxter has already had to deal with the absence of Andile Jali and Bongani Zungu, both of whom are suspended for Friday’s game against Senegal. READ: Bafana may be without Khune for WC qualifiers Kaizer Chiefs duo Siphiwe Tshabalala and Mulomowandau Mathoho, have been called up to the squad and joined training in Polokwane on Tuesday morning.  African News Agency